It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the use of phoneme posterior probability features, which are related to language processing. 

Additionally, it involves the use of machine learning techniques such as support vector machines and PLDA, which are related to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, as the paper deals with security and countermeasures, it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
